<h1>Community</h1>

<p>
Clever Harold is <a href="http://www.gnu.org/licenses/gpl.html">Free
Software</a>, which means that it's source code is open to everyone.
We invite you to participate by asking questions, submitting patches
and bug reports, and of course making suggestions.
</p>

<p>
If you're a developer or designer, we invite you to participate at all
levels of the project.  We need more eyes, more code, and many more pixels
to make Clever Harold better.
</p>


<h3><a name="mailinglist">Mailing List</a></h3>

<p>
The mailing list for Clever Harold is hosted
by <a href="http://groups.google.com">Google Groups</a>.
</p>

<p>
You can <a href="http://groups.google.com/group/cleverharold">browse
the list here</a>.
</p>

<p>
<form action="http://groups.google.com/group/cleverharold/boxsubscribe"
      class="f-wrap-1">
You can subscribe to the list here:
    <label for="email">Your Email Address</label>
    <input type="text" name="email" id="email" /> 
    <input type="submit" />
</form>
</p>


<h3><a name="wiki">Wiki</a></h3>

Extra documentation, examples, more are on
the <a href="http://trac.cleverharold.org/wiki">Clever Harold
Wiki</a>.

<h3><a name="trac">Trac</a></h3>

Get the latest code, submit requests for bug fixes and feature
enhancements, and monitor the progress of the Clever Harold project
from the <a href="http://trac.cleverharold.org/">Clever Harold
Trac</a>.

